The Transport Layer breaks large application data into segments before transmission.

The receiving host performs reassembly, restoring the original data.

During encapsulation, TCP or UDP headers are added before forwarding data to the Network Layer.

Cybersecurity Relevance

Many IDS/IPS systems reconstruct fragmented traffic before inspecting it because attackers intentionally fragment packets to evade detection.

Tools
Wireshark
tcpdump
Suricata
Snort
Blue Team (Defenders)

Process: Enable stream reassembly and fragmented packet inspection to detect hidden malicious payloads.

End Goal: Prevent IDS evasion through packet fragmentation.

Red Team (Attackers)

Process: Fragment malicious payloads across multiple packets to bypass poorly configured intrusion detection systems.

End Goal: Deliver malicious payloads without triggering security alerts.
